<div id="content" lang="en" dir="ltr">
<a href="./MayLith">MayLith</a>: I just saw this over on oook. Looks like a bug to me! <p>
<a href="./angband.oook.cz/screen-show.php?id=551">http://angband.oook.cz/screen-show.php?id=551</a> 
</p>
<hr>
 <p>
I've had one of those, and the reward I choose was a player's corpse (the other rewards were boring). I've been infinitely eating from the player's corpse ever since (they don't run out of meat!). 
</p>
<p>
Later I used the multiply power of my symbiote to get more. I will try with a morphic oil or mimic powers if I get the chance. (-; 
</p>
<p>
Any situation where the player meets himself or his corpse are quite absurd. 
</p>
<hr>
 <a href="./MayLith">MayLith</a>: The quest was for two Players... which means you'd have to kill two Players to get a reward. I've never run into a Player wandering around the dungeon, myself or otherwise. <p>
<a href="./NeilStevens">NeilStevens</a>: It is known that some people run into weird quests when going very deep. 
</p>
<p>
<a href="./MayLith">MayLith</a>: Does that make this a known behavior rather than a known bug, then? Just asking for the sake of the information. 
</p>
<p>
<a href="./NeilStevens">NeilStevens</a>: It's a known bug that nobody has felt like/been able to fix. 
</p>
<p>
<a href="./MayLith">MayLith</a>: Are the location(s) and/or nature(s) of the bug known?  
</p>
<p>
<a href="./NeilStevens">NeilStevens</a>: Not that I know of. 
</p>
<p>
<a href="./MayLith">MayLith</a>: Ah, okay, thanks. (I've got enough to do as it is. &lt;g&gt;) 
</p>
<p>
<a href="./MassimilianoMarangio">MassimilianoMarangio</a>: A test for 1 &lt;= dungeon level &lt;= 98 was missing in the code for the quest list display. Fixed in ToME 2.3.0 (CVS). 
</p>
<p>
<a href="./NeilStevens">NeilStevens</a>: You really are the hero of ToME.  Truly.   Your bugfixing is monumental. 
</p>
<p>
<a href="./MayLith">MayLith</a>: Amen to that! 
</p>
